What you need to know:  This is not the first time Carrefour is finding itself in hot water over its relations with suppliers.In 2021, the Competition Tribunal reinforced CAK’s order for Carrefour to revise all its agreements with some 700 suppliers after a tribunal found it has been exploiting traders. The retail giant was also barred from delisting suppliers unilaterally without notice for failure to meet its stringent supply contract.